    "body": "Fix the cursor style terminfo capability (should be Se, not se). Also include foot in the list of terminals that supports setting and resetting cursor style (see\r\nhttps://codeberg.org/dnkl/foot/issues/797#issuecomment-280305)\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> update the faq?\r\n> \r\n> https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/869e55f2aacdc986a51f0bb683f11dcf0c464e98/runtime/doc/faq.txt#L101\r\n\r\nI think we should keep that for now, because not all terminals implement the reset properly (for instance, xterm and terminals which copy xterm use `CSI 2 <sp> q`, which just makes the cursor back into a block again). According to https://codeberg.org/dnkl/foot/issues/797#issuecomment-280305 they _should_ support `CSI <sp> q` and report that in their terminfo.",
