        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@shushtain I tried to guess how to apply that hint: starting with\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/tui/terminfo_defs.h b/src/nvim/tui/terminfo_defs.h\r\nindex baf516b177..1d4d450486 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/tui/terminfo_defs.h\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/tui/terminfo_defs.h\r\n@@ -508,7 +508,7 @@ static const TerminfoEntry tmux_256colour_terminfo = {\r\n     [kTerm_set_attributes] = \"\\033[0%?%p6%t;1%;%?%p2%t;4%;%?%p1%p3%|%t;7%;%?%p4%t;5%;%?%p5%t;2%;%?%p7%t;8%;m%?%p9%t^N%e\\017%;\",\r\n     [kTerm_set_lr_margin] = NULL,\r\n     [kTerm_to_status_line] = \"\\033]0;\",\r\n-    [kTerm_reset_cursor_style] = \"\\033[2 q\",\r\n+    [kTerm_reset_cursor_style] = \"\\033Ptmux;\\033\\033[2 q\\033\\\\\",\r\n     [kTerm_set_cursor_style] = \"\\033[%p1%d q\",\r\n     [kTerm_enter_strikethrough_mode] = \"\\033[9m\",\r\n     [kTerm_set_rgb_foreground] = NULL,\r\n```\r\nthen replacing `2` with `5` or `6` (not being sure what both the values mean, although I have seen https://vt100.net/docs/vt510-rm/DECSCUSR.html), but the cursor stays steady block after exiting. \r\n\r\nIn practice after executing bash command `printf \"\\033[%d q\" $n` I get steady block for `n=2` like in the above docs, and (blinking and steady, respectively) vertical bar for (undocumented there) `5` and `6`. \r\n\r\nI also have no knowledge how Tmux passes it to the parent terminal, so I just tried the above wrapper (maybe incorrectly). \r\n\r\nFor clarity: I have `TERM=tmux-256color` in the shell where I tested these changes. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
